-- ThyssenKrupp Chief Sees Steel Demand Staying Strong, Financial Times Says
-- B y   V i c t o r i a   B a t c h e l o r
-- 2010-09-29T23:18:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/thyssenkrupp-chief-sees-steel-demand-staying-strong-financial-times-says.html
ThyssenKrupp AG Chief Executive
Officer Ekkehard Schulz said steel demand from the car,
electronic and household appliances industries is “very
strong” and will be maintained into next year, the Financial
Times reported, citing an interview.  He said the company would “reach the higher end of its
profit guidance” for its fiscal year ending Sept. 30, the FT
reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Batchelor at 
 vbatchelor@bloomberg.net  